**CORRECTED CODE**:

```
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main(){
  string s;
  long long n;
  cin >> s >> n;
  for(int i=0; i<n; ++i){
    long long si = s[i] - '0';
    if(si>1){
      cout << si << endl;
      return 0;
    }
  }
  cout << 1 << endl;
}
```
Explanation: 

The given code is almost correct, but the variable `n`, which represents the number of characters to be checked, should be of type `long long` to accommodate the upper constraint of `K` being `10^18`.